<div id="review_2693566262" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2693566262" />
    <a title="Rishi Prakash" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2173246-rishi-prakash"><img alt="Rishi Prakash" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1632136563p2/2173246.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2693566262?book_show_action=true">Feb 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rishi Prakash" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rishi Prakash" href="/user/show/2173246-rishi-prakash">Rishi Prakash</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780007201792" href="/book/show/6362191-bones-of-the-hills">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2693566262" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15280904556354503812">This is the third book in a 5 book series. The series is like a historical fiction surrounding the rise of the Mongol Nation. The first three books in the series focus on Genghis Khan so this was the last book on him. It is a great comeback after kind of boring 2nd book! <br/><br/>The author added a section in back clarifying where he augmented history which I really appreciated. Iggulden is a great story teller and also a brilliant researcher which comes out clearly in the books. <br/><br/>This book, like those th</span>
  <span id="freeText15280904556354503812" style="display:none">This is the third book in a 5 book series. The series is like a historical fiction surrounding the rise of the Mongol Nation. The first three books in the series focus on Genghis Khan so this was the last book on him. It is a great comeback after kind of boring 2nd book! <br /><br />The author added a section in back clarifying where he augmented history which I really appreciated. Iggulden is a great story teller and also a brilliant researcher which comes out clearly in the books. <br /><br />This book, like those that precede it, is absolutely fantastic. Once again, the reader is plunged into the Mongol campaign as they scourge across the land, lured from the Chin lands to the dry deserts of the middle east. You’ll be right along side Genghis as he and his brothers tackle the new challenges of foreign lands and new enemies. The characters are probably the strong point which is really saying something because the story is phenomenal here as well. I found myself genuinely caring what happened to each and every character, riding the highs and lows right along with them. And there are a lot of highs and lows here.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15280904556354503812" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

