<span id="freeTextContainer634932262900624110">This is a wonderful series of books that continues its momentum through this the third volume. It&apos;s amazing how drawn to the key characters you become even though, for the most part, almost everyone of them is brutal and unforgiving. The story races through to the end of Genghis&apos; life with more plotting, intrigue and dramatic war scenes. You almost have to pause for breath at the end to take stock of it all. I look forward to reading the last two books in the series which carry on the next stage</span>
  <span id="freeText634932262900624110" style="display:none">This is a wonderful series of books that continues its momentum through this the third volume. It's amazing how drawn to the key characters you become even though, for the most part, almost everyone of them is brutal and unforgiving. The story races through to the end of Genghis' life with more plotting, intrigue and dramatic war scenes. You almost have to pause for breath at the end to take stock of it all. I look forward to reading the last two books in the series which carry on the next stages of the development of the Mongol nation through Genghis' heirs. </span>
