    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_686381911" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/686381911" />
    <a title="Graham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1760824-graham"><img alt="Graham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1380743323p2/1760824.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/686381911?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Graham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Graham" href="/user/show/1760824-graham">Graham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1760824-graham?shelf=asia">asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1760824-graham?shelf=war">war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1760824-graham?shelf=historical">historical</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer686381911" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2126841825292762220">The third instalment of Conn Iggulden&apos;s Conqueror series and the final part of his Genghis trilogy. Having finished - for the moment - conquering northern China, Genghis takes his armies west to invade the Middle East.<br/><br/>Once again, Iggulden delivers an incredibly readable novel of historical warfare. The story is action-packed with inventive and fluidly-written battle sequences, each different from the last. There are no repetitive scenarios here; instead, the author strives to deliver something d</span>
  <span id="freeText2126841825292762220" style="display:none">The third instalment of Conn Iggulden's Conqueror series and the final part of his Genghis trilogy. Having finished - for the moment - conquering northern China, Genghis takes his armies west to invade the Middle East.<br /><br />Once again, Iggulden delivers an incredibly readable novel of historical warfare. The story is action-packed with inventive and fluidly-written battle sequences, each different from the last. There are no repetitive scenarios here; instead, the author strives to deliver something different each time. The Muslim 'enemy', given their own point-of-view scenes, are the most interesting yet, providing plenty of thrills as Genghis realises he's bitten off more than he can chew. The claustrophobic assault on a mountain stronghold is the novel's highlight.<br /><br />As ever, there's plenty of intrigue between Genghis's expanding family, as the author sets up the pieces for future books; Jochi is a clear favourite of mine. What I found most interesting, though, is the character of Genghis himself, who has developed unexpectedly throughout the three books. <br /><br />In WOLF OF THE PLAINS, Genghis was the clear hero, fighting for survival against the odds and banding the tribes together against a common enemy. In LORDS OF THE BOW, he became an anti-hero, laying cities to waste, driven by a burning vengeance and becoming colder and more impassive at each turn. In BONES OF THE HILLS, the transformation is now complete and Genghis is a clear villain, an inhuman character for whom death and destruction is a way of life. Thus the ending of the novel is extremely satisfying.<br /><br />A fourth novel, EMPIRE OF SILVER, follows.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2126841825292762220" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

